latestReviews.body:
LGTM, thanks for simplifying and fixing this.

Few notes:
1. How did you test this? May be let the nightly run on a local branch, and predefine the mapping separately. When the results are uploaded you will see if mapping is working.
2. Will the auto-expand policy not impact in any adverse way right now, if no data is ingested in RAW_CASE_TABLE? 
3. I suggest not to merge this change on Friday, and try to get this on Monday, so that we actively can track and fix any issues.

comments.body: @prsunny  FYI
Thanks for the improvement

Can you please check other place too so that you can remove the definition too?
```
DEFAULT_BOOT_TIMEOUT = 300
DEFAULT_INTERVAL = 60
```

> Can you please check other place too so that you can remove the definition too?
> 
> ```
> DEFAULT_BOOT_TIMEOUT = 300
> DEFAULT_INTERVAL = 60
> ```

For DEFAULT_BOOT_TIMEOUT, it has already used wait_until to wait system-health bootup.
I update test_service_checker to call wait_until as well, for these checking expected value for once, it's efficient to call wait_until, but for checking unexpected value, wait_until is not a good choice.
For example, in test_system_health_config, it has to wait fixed time to make sure db is refreshed, then check if db doesn't have some unexpected value. We can't use wait_until to do this thing, if for first time, it doesn't have specified value, maybe it's because db is not refreshed, not new config file works. So I don't touch test_system_health_config and test_device_checker. 
I also think it's better to use a global variable to record timeout, if in future, system-health changes refresh interval, it's easy to sync timeout value.
I define WAIT_TIMEOUT = 90 in this script.

@arlakshm - this is reverting https://github.com/Azure/sonic-mgmt/pull/4728 - which we required to make the test pass on a T2 chassis. PR#4728 was done as SONiC code does not create snmp objects when route is pointing to internal ports (https://github.com/Azure/sonic-snmpagent/blob/a07da536186a9d9698ec63ec3b1e75bef097ae00/src/sonic_ax_impl/mibs/ietf/rfc4292.py#L82)

Can you please check into it

> @arlakshm - this is reverting #4728 - which we required to make the test pass on a T2 chassis. PR#4728 was done as SONiC code does not create snmp objects when route is pointing to internal ports (https://github.com/Azure/sonic-snmpagent/blob/a07da536186a9d9698ec63ec3b1e75bef097ae00/src/sonic_ax_impl/mibs/ietf/rfc4292.py#L82)
> 
> Can you please check into it

@sanmalho-git, I verified SNMP ipCidrRouteTable has the default route even if the route is learnt from another linecard. Please the PR description with the output collected for this case.
In SNMP the nexthop is ignored if the port role in internal(`INT`). In case of voq chassis the Inband port will have a role of Inband(`Inb`) so the routes are added to ipCidrRouteTable even if they are learnt from another linecard.

@arlakshm In our port_config.ini, we had defined the port role for Inband port to be 'Int' and not 'Inb'. We will make the appropriate change and test.. 

Your change is good.
